[1
Date: Thu, 15 Mar 2001 18:34:20 +0200
From: Andrew Jamieson <aj.plett@pixie.co.za>
Source: PANA, 15 Mar 2001 [edited

Bubonic Plague Kills 11 People in Zambia
----------------------------------------
The deadly bubonic plague has claimed 11 lives in the last one week in
Petauke, Eastern Zambia, where another 30 patients are fighting for their
lives, according to health officials.
Health Minister Enoch Kavindele said Wednesday that health experts have
brought some tissues for testing at the University Teaching Hospital
laboratory in Lusaka. The Central Board of Health (CBoH), which has
confirmed the outbreak, said it had already dispatched a team of experts to
the area.
CBoH spokesman Ben Chirwa said Tuesday that the strain of the disease in
Petauke is the type that manifests in the blood stream and results in
fatality if not treated immediately. The symptoms of the disease, which
kills within 3 days, include swollen glands and high fever.
[Bubonic plague was first reported Zambia's western Zambezi in 1936. The
most serious outbreak was in 1997 in Namwala, where it claimed more than 25
lives.
--
