Source: Times of Zambia Internet Version 15 Mar 01 [edited
<http://www.times.co.zm/>

Zambia: Outbreak of bubonic plague reportedly spreading
-------------------------------------------------------
Seven more people have died from bubonic plague at the Nyanje Mission
Hospital in Petauke in the last few days, bringing the total death toll to
18 as the disease has now spread to Sinda. The number of admissions at the
Nyanje hospital has also swelled to 44.
Hospital administrator Jack Phiri confirmed the development yesterday but
could not however give details on how many cases were referred to the
hospital from Sinda. He said patients at the hospital were responding to
treatment and that some would be discharged soon.

Director general of the Central Board of Health (CBoH) Gavin Silwamba said
of those admitted, 9 children were below the age of 9 years, 31 were aged
above 5 years. Fifty-eight patients had so far been treated.

Dr Silwamba said specimens sent to the UTH confirmed the presence of
_Yersinia pestis_ the causative agent of the plague.

He appealed to people in the affected areas not to touch dead rats with
their bare hands, block holes in houses, kill as many rats and reduce their
population, then bury or burn them and seek medical attention quickly.
--
Pierre Bigras
