[Although the comment in [1 concerning strain characteristics is somewhat
cryptic, it may be referring to _Yersinia pestis_ strains that express V
and W antigens. Expression of these proteins is controlled by plasmid genes
and they are two of a number of virulence factors that have been correlated
with rapid proliferation and overwhelming sepsis. Further information about
the isolates would be appreciated. - Mod.ES
